球队分析

2022-12-22

Variances

EFG_O: Effective Field Goal Percentage Shot
EFG_D: Effective Field Goal Percentage Allowed
TOR: Turnover Percentage Allowed (Turnover Rate)
TORD: Turnover Percentage Committed (Steal Rate)
ORB: Offensive Rebound Rate
DRB: Offensive Rebound Rate Allowed
FTR : Free Throw Rate (How often the given team shoots Free Throws)
FTRD: Free Throw Rate Allowed
2P_O: Two-Point Shooting Percentage
2P_D: Two-Point Shooting Percentage Allowed
3P_O: Three-Point Shooting Percentage
3P_D: Three-Point Shooting Percentage Allowed
ADJ_T: Adjusted Tempo (An estimate of the tempo (possessions per 40 minutes) a team would have against the team that wants to play at an average Division I tempo)
WAB: Wins Above Bubble (The bubble refers to the cut off between making the NCAA March Madness Tournament and not making it)

cbb <- read.csv('cbb.csv')
print(colnames(cbb))

Correlation Coefficient Matrix

corr <- round(cor(cbb[, 5:21]), 1)
ggcorrplot(corr, hc.order = TRUE, 
           type = "lower", 
           lab = TRUE, 
           lab_size = 2, 
           tl.cex = 10,
           method="circle", 
           colors = c("tomato2", "white", "springgreen3"), 
           title="Correlogram of data", 
           ggtheme=theme_bw)

WAB, X2P_O, EFG_O, and X3P_O are strongly positive related to ADJOE. While TOR is negative related to ADJOE, and EFG_D, X2P_D, FTRD and DRB are a little negative related to ADJOE.

corr1 <- round(cor(cbb[, c('WAB', 'X2P_O', 'EFG_O', 'X3P_O', 'TOR',                      'EFG_D', 'X2P_D', 'FTRD', 'DRB')]), 1)
ggcorrplot(corr1, hc.order = TRUE, 
           type = "lower", 
           lab = TRUE, 
           lab_size = 3, 
           tl.cex = 10,
           method="circle", 
           colors = c("tomato2", "white", "springgreen3"), 
           title="Correlogram of variances related to ADJOE", 
           ggtheme=theme_bw)

For ADJDE, X2P_D, X3P_D and EFG_D are strongly positive related to ADJDE, while DRB is a little positive related to ADJDE. On the other hand, WAB are strongly negative related to ADJDE, while ORB and TORD are a little negative related to ADJDE.

m_adjoe <- lm(ADJOE~WAB+EFG_O+EFG_D+TOR+TORD+DRB+ORB+FTR, data=cbb)
summary(m_adjoe)

## Call:
## lm(formula = ADJOE ~ WAB + EFG_O + EFG_D + TOR + TORD + DRB + 
##     ORB + FTR, data = cbb)
## 
## Residuals:

## -7.5638 -1.3474  0.0047  1.3460  7.8916 
## 
## Coefficients:
##              Estimate Std. Error t value Pr(>|t|)    
## (Intercept) 48.714530   1.524586  31.953  < 2e-16 ***
## WAB          0.643662   0.013328  48.295  < 2e-16 ***
## EFG_O        0.852157   0.019823  42.988  < 2e-16 ***
## EFG_D        0.469380   0.020902  22.456  < 2e-16 ***
## TOR         -0.857523   0.026328 -32.571  < 2e-16 ***
## TORD        -0.498525   0.021582 -23.099  < 2e-16 ***
## DRB          0.198763   0.015256  13.028  < 2e-16 ***
## ORB          0.389387   0.012900  30.185  < 2e-16 ***
## FTR          0.041582   0.008633   4.817 1.55e-06 ***
## ---
## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1
## 
## Residual standard error: 2.075 on 2446 degrees of freedom
## Multiple R-squared:  0.9212, Adjusted R-squared:  0.9209 
## F-statistic:  3573 on 8 and 2446 DF,  p-value: < 2.2e-16
df_adjoe <- data.frame(coefficients=c('WAB', 'EFG_O', 'EFG_D', 'TOR', 'TORD', 'DRB','ORB', 'FTR'), value=c(0.643662, 0.852157, 0.469380, -0.857523, -0.498525, 0.198763, 0.389387, 0.041582))

df_adjoe$coefficients <- factor(df_adjoe$coefficients, levels=df_adjoe$coefficients)

ggplot(df_adjoe, aes(x=coefficients, y=value))+
  geom_bar(stat='identity', width=.5, fill="tomato3")+
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle=65, vjust=0.6))+
  geom_text(aes(label=round(value,3)), 
            position = position_dodge2(width = 0.9, preserve = 'single'),
            vjust = -0.2, hjust = 0.5)+
  labs(title="Relevant Factors of Adjusted Offensive Efficiency", 
          caption="Source: cbb")

According to analysis, EFG_O and TOR are the most two important factors. If we improve 1 point of EFG_O, we can increase almost 0.852 for Adjusted Offensive Efficiency. However, if TOR increase 1 point, the Adjusted Offensive Efficiency will decrease 0.858.

For North Carolina, they are very good at ADJOE. The minimum ADJOE of North Carolina is even higher than 3rd Qu of all teams, which is a very high score in NCAA. According to the model, EFG_O and TOR are the two most important factors that effect ADJOE. North Carolina’s mean EFG_O is higher than most of teams’, and mean TOR is lower than most of teams’.
